\section{Timing shapes}{

The timing constructors are pure shapes — they describe \emph{when} an event
fires and carry no other config:
\itemize{
\item \code{wire_immediate()}: Fires on every event with no rate limiting.
\item \code{wire_throttle(ms, leading)}: Fires at most every \code{ms} milliseconds
while the event is active.
\item \code{wire_debounce(ms)}: Waits until the user pauses for \code{ms} milliseconds
before firing.
